AGI -&nbsp;Sergio Mattarella> deposed this morning a crown of bay in homage to the Unknown Milite. Then he held his hand to the representatives of the fighting associations deployed at the Altar of the Homeland, who presented himself citing cities and bodies of belonging. Thus the President of the Republic - who in late morning reached Genoa - opened in Rome the celebrations for the eighteenth anniversary of the Liberation > - in the course of the traditional ceremony to which they took part, in addition to the presidents of the Senate and the Chamber, Ignazio La Russo and Lorenzo Fontana >, also the President of the Council, Giorgia&nbsp;Meloni,> together with the Minister of Defense, Guido&nbsp;Crosetto >, and the President of the President of the Costuzionale Corte For the Head of State the event today marked the return to public commitments after the very recent intervention for the plant of a pacemaker. At the end of the ceremony, at the foot of the staircase of the Altare della Patria, it is time for everyone to leave, in that suspended atmosphere >che, while respecting the traditional ceremonial of the institutional appointment, involves a little everything in a Rome where, just a few hundred meters away, winds the river of people who make the last homage to Pope Francis.
<h2> Meloni, "reaffirmed democratic values denied by fascism"
"Today Italy celebrates the 80th Anniversary of Liberation. On this day, the nation honors its rediscovered freedom > and reaffirms the centrality of those democratic values which the fascist regime had denied and which for seventy-seven years have been engraved in the Republican Constitution." So Premier Meloni, in a passage of the statement diffused by Palazzo Chigi.
&nbsp;
<div </div
